         <abstract>
            <p>Some very fast numerical methods have been developed in recent years for the solution of elliptic differential equations which allow for separation of variables. In this paper, a Fourier-Toeplitz method is developed as an alternative to the well-known methods of Hockney and Buneman. It is based on the fast Fourier transform and Toeplitz factorizations. The use of Toeplitz factorizations combined with the Sherman-Morrison formula is also systematically explored for linear systems of algebraic equations with band matrices of Toeplitz, or almost Toeplitz form. Finally, results of numerical experiments are described.</p>
          </abstract>
